content.location: Locate the SE corner of the buttress. Climb the groove to a overhang, pass the overhang on the left.

content.description: A good route, in three distinct parts.  The lower face is juggy, but not without a puzzle.  Above the first ledge is a gorgeous crack (with an old fixed nut).  Above the second ledge is a face.  Go left for 5.8, right to the corner for 5.9.  Straight up the middle looks challenging!
content.protection: As described in Swartling & Mayer, not much on the bottom and top sections, but great gear in the middle section.
content.location: Left of the gully splitting the twin buttresses, left of the boulder below "West Siam" and "Sven Golly", and left of the easy route through the pine gully is a juggy face.  Start here

content.description: Up the first few feet of "West Siam".  Where there are jugs on the face to your left, move left and continue straight up.
content.protection: TR, otherwise none to speak of.
content.location: Start in the same spot as "West Siam".

content.description: A fun little exploration.  Up the left side of the juggy lower face.  For the middle, step around the corner to the left and use the crack in the dihedral.  For the upper step, use the left edge of the face (easier than it may look) or go around the corner to the left and easier ground.
content.protection: None for the easy first step.  Good gear on the middle step.  The upper step depends on you choice of finish.
content.location: Start from the bench to the left of Siam gully.

pathTokens: East Bluff 02 - East of the Quarry

content.description: A few lines to do on your way to Prayer Wall and beyond.
